sections.text:
Socio-demographic characteristics considered for this study were: age – adolescents and young adults aged between 12 and 40;
Frontiers in Psychology 04 frontiersin.org
gender was categorized into female and male; education was divided into secondary or below, higher secondary, and bachelor’s degree or above; marital status – married and unmarried; occupation was classified as student, job holder, business, and homemaker, and monthly family income was represented in dollar in this study.
